 <section id="about" class="about-section">
 <h2 class="section-title">Our Mission</h2>
 <div class="about-content">
 <p>Hi, I'm <span class="founder-name">Ethan Moran</span>, a junior at Buckingham Browne & Nichols School in Cambridge, Massachusetts. While standardized testing like the SAT definitely isn't a measure of intelligence, it is important for college admissions and can significantly impact your future opportunities.</p>

 <p>The major issue? Access to tutoring. With companies charging over $200 per hour, quality test prep just isn't accessible to most families. When you look at the data, there's a clear trend: wealthier students score higher, not because they're smarter, but because they can afford expensive tutoring.</p>

 <p>I created Mass Tutoring to break this cycle. By connecting experienced high school tutors (who scored 1530+ on the SAT) with students who need help, we're making quality test prep accessible to everyoneâ€”regardless of economics.</p>

 <p>Both our tutors and students benefit: students get the help they need to reach their academic goals, while tutors gain valuable teaching experience, give back to their community, and help level the playing field.</p>
